The paper deals with the cryptanalysis of rank-based cryptography, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also involves algebraic modeling and solving of linear systems, which are topics in information theory (cs.IT) and systems and control (cs.SY). The use of combinatorial and algebraic approaches also relates to discrete mathematics (cs.DS). Finally, the paper involves optimization and complexity analysis, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG).
